                    type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Course","name":"BUILD - 3-Year BBA in Entrepreneurship","description":"A 3-year undergraduate program in entrepreneurship with practitioner-led teaching, startup incubation, and 100+ mentors.","provider":{"@type":"Organization","name":"IIAT Hyderabad","url":"https://iiath.com"},"url":"https://iiath.com/programs/ug","timeRequired":"P3Y","courseMode":"Onsite","offers":{"@type":"Offer","price":2620780,"priceCurrency":"INR","availability":"https://schema.org/InStock"}}</script>
                <script
                    type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Who is eligible to apply for the IIAT programs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our programs are designed for diverse learners. The K12 programs welcome students aged 6-18, UG programs are for ages 18-24, LEAD programs target professionals aged 21-45 with business experience, and SEED programs cater to young innovators aged 14-20. Each program has specific requirements tailored to its objectives."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there specific sectors that applicants must focus on?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No, we welcome students and entrepreneurs from all sectors. Our programs are designed to support diverse interests and industries, from technology and healthcare to education, sustainability, arts, and social impact. We believe in cross-disciplinary learning and innovation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is there any international exposure in the programs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, all our programs include international exposure through virtual sessions with global mentors, case studies from international markets, collaborative projects with international students, and potential opportunities for international competitions, exchanges, and business trips for advanced learners."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the duration of each program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Program durations vary: K12 programs run for full academic years with continuous enrollment, UG programs span 3 years with semester-based learning, LEAD programs are intensive 6-12 month courses, and SEED programs offer flexible 3-6 month modules. All programs include ongoing mentorship and alumni support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What kind of support do students receive after completing the program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We provide comprehensive post-program support including lifetime access to our alumni network, ongoing career guidance, entrepreneurship mentorship, access to funding networks, continued learning resources, and invitations to exclusive events, workshops, and masterclasses."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the minimum educational requirements?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Requirements vary by program: K12 programs require current school enrollment, UG programs need high school completion (10+2), LEAD programs prefer a bachelor's degree or equivalent professional experience, and SEED programs welcome students from grades 3-12. We also consider exceptional candidates with demonstrated talent and passion."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can international students apply?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Absolutely! International students are welcome to apply to all our programs. We provide support for visa applications, have flexible options for remote/hybrid participation, offer orientation programs for international students, and maintain a diverse global community of learners from over 30 countries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is work or entrepreneurial experience mandatory for LEAD program?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"While work or entrepreneurial experience is highly preferred for the LEAD program, we also consider candidates in the ideation phase with strong business concepts. We look for demonstrated passion, leadership potential, problem-solving abilities, and commitment to making an impact in their chosen field."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there age restrictions for any programs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, each program has age guidelines: K12 (6-18 years), UG (18-24 years), LEAD (21-45 years), and SEED (14-20 years). However, we consider exceptional cases on an individual basis. Age requirements ensure appropriate peer groups, curriculum depth, and career relevance for each cohort."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the admission process?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our holistic admission process includes: (1) Online application with academic records, (2) Statement of purpose or business idea submission, (3) Aptitude assessment or portfolio review, (4) Interview with our expert panel, and (5) Final selection based on merit, potential, diversity, and program fit. The entire process takes 3-4 weeks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When does the next batch start?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our programs have rolling admissions throughout the year. Our Undergraduate Program Starts in july, and LEAD and SEED are round the year"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How competitive is the selection process?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our programs maintain high standards with acceptance rates varying by program: approximately 30-40% for K12, 25-35% for UG, 20-30% for LEAD, and 35-45% for SEED. We look for academic excellence, passion, unique perspectives, leadership potential, and alignment with program values rather than just grades."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I apply for multiple programs simultaneously?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, you can apply to multiple programs if you meet the eligibility criteria for each. However, we recommend focusing on the program that best aligns with your current goals and stage of development. Our admissions team can provide personalized guidance during the application process."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the program fee structure?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Fee varies by program and duration, All fees include curriculum materials, mentorship, platform access, and certificates. Detailed breakdown is provided during admissions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are scholarships available?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! We offer merit and need based scholarships. Scholarships are awarded based on academic excellence, financial need, unique talent, diversity, and exceptional potential."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What payment options are available?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We offer flexible payment options including: one-time full payment (with discount), semester/module-wise payments, monthly EMI plans (0% interest for eligible students), education loans through partner banks, corporate sponsorships, and installment plans. Our finance team works with each family to create a feasible payment structure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the refund policy?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, we have a refund policy.The admission team will share detailed refund terms during the admission process."}}]}</script>
